7. System Architecture

7.1 Component Stack

```
LAYER 4: Presentation Layer
   ├── Auditor Dashboard
   ├── Policy Simulation Interface
   └── Public Transparency Portal

LAYER 3: Cognitive Layer
   ├── Constrained LLM (Ψ-guarded)
   ├── Explanation Generator
   └── Anomaly Hypothesis Engine

LAYER 2: Analytic Layer
   ├── Temporal Hypergraph Engine
   ├── Ψ-Core Reasoner
   ├── Entropy Calculator (S-AGE)
   ├── Corruption Detector (CCI/GND)
   └── Risk Aggregator (CSRI)

LAYER 1: Data Layer
   ├── Budget/Procurement Ingestor
   ├── Legal Corpus Parser
   ├── Macroeconomic Data Hub
   └── Institutional Database
```

7.2 Data Flow

```
Raw Data → Hypergraph Constructor → PFH(t)
                                  ↓
                         Ψ-Core Validator
                                  ↓
                    Analytic Modules (parallel)
                    ├── S-AGE Calculator
                    ├── CCI Computer
                    ├── GND Evaluator
                    └── CSRI Aggregator
                                  ↓
                         Cognitive Reasoner
                    (Generates hypotheses/explanations)
                                  ↓
                         Visualization/Alerting
```

7.3 Implementation Specifications

7.3.1 Hypergraph Storage

```
PFH Schema:
   - vertices: UUID, type, attributes (JSON)
   - hyperedges: UUID, timestamp, vertices[], 
                 weights, labels, legal_refs[]
   - layers: name, schema_def
```

7.3.2 Ψ-Core Implementation

```python
class PsiCore:
    def __init__(self, legal_corpus):
        self.rules = parse_legal_corpus(legal_corpus)
        self.knowledge_graph = build_legal_kg(self.rules)
    
    def validate(self, hyperedge):
        applicable_rules = self.match_rules(hyperedge)
        for rule in applicable_rules:
            if not self.satisfies(hyperedge, rule):
                return False, rule
        return True, None
```

7.3.3 CCI Computation

```python
def compute_CCI(PFH, window_size=12):
    CCI_scores = {}
    for v in PFH.vertices:
        centrality_series = []
        for t in range(-window_size, 0):
            C_H = compute_centrality(PFH, v, t)
            centrality_series.append(C_H)
        
        mu = np.mean(centrality_series[:-1])
        sigma = np.std(centrality_series[:-1])
        CCI = abs(centrality_series[-1] - mu) / sigma
        CCI_scores[v] = CCI
    
    return CCI_scores
```

