8. Validation Framework

8.1 Synthetic Data Generation

Algorithm 8.1.1 (Corruption Simulation).

```
1. Generate baseline PFH₀ (clean state)
2. Inject corruption patterns:
   a. Shell company cascades
   b. Bid-rigging rotations  
   c. Inflated procurement
3. Let system evolve via agent-based simulation
4. Record resulting PFH_corrupt(t)
```

8.2 Detection Metrics

Definition 8.2.1 (Corruption Detection Performance).

· True Positive Rate: TPR = #detected_corrupt_edges / #total_corrupt_edges
· False Positive Rate: FPR = #false_alarms / #clean_edges
· Early Warning Lead Time: Δt_warning = t_detection - t_corruption_start

8.3 Sovereign Crisis Prediction

Validation Protocol:

1. Train on historical data [t₀, t_train]
2. Compute CSRI(t) for t ∈ [t_train, t_test]
3. Compare against actual crisis dates C = {c₁, c₂, ...}
4. Calculate:
   · Precision: P = #true_crises_predicted / #total_predictions
   · Recall: R = #crises_predicted / #total_crises
   · Lead Time: L = average(t_prediction - t_crisis)

