9. Mathematical Appendix

9.1 Hypergraph Isomorphism for Corruption Patterns

Definition 9.1.1 (Pattern Matching).
Two sub-hypergraphs H₁, H₂ are isomorphic if ∃ bijection φ: V₁ → V₂ such that:

1. ∀v ∈ V₁: type(v) = type(φ(v))
2. ∀e₁ = (t₁, I₁, ...) ∈ E₁, ∃e₂ = (t₂, I₂, ...) ∈ E₂ with:
   · |t₁ - t₂| < ε_t
   · φ(I₁) = I₂ (vertex mapping)
   · |ω(e₁) - ω(e₂)|/ω(e₁) < ε_ω

9.2 Entropy Calculus

Theorem 9.2.1 (S-AGE Decomposition).

```
S-AGE(t) = S-AGE_structure(t) + S-AGE_magnitude(t) + S-AGE_timing(t)
```

where:

· S-AGE_structure: Entropy of hypergraph topology
· S-AGE_magnitude: Entropy of weight distribution
· S-AGE_timing: Entropy of temporal patterns

Proof: Follows from chain rule of entropy: H(X,Y,Z) = H(X) + H(Y|X) + H(Z|X,Y). ∎

9.3 Ψ-Core Completeness

Theorem 9.3.1 (Legal Coverage).
For any legal system with finite statutes, ∃ finite Ψ-Core such that:

```
∀ hyperedge e: legal(e) ⇔ Ψ-Core validates e
```

Proof Sketch: Construct Ψ-Core by including all legal provisions. Finiteness ensures computational tractability. ∎

